obfuscation: Oh't be you is it, and what are ye shiverin ' 'bout; as stay by the cook where ye belong and ye 'll find no necessity of chatterin ', and it 's c-c-cold, and which d 'ye think it were-- the Old Man, and none o ' your lip young un or I will learn ye.
original: Oh, 'tis you, is it? What're ye shiverin' 'bout? Stay by the stove where ye belong and ye'll find no need of chatterin'. It's c-c-cold. Who d'ye think it were--the Old Man? None o' your lip, young un, or I'll learn ye.

obfuscation: Where was it ye have been all o ' time-- fo'c's'tle, yes, and let Old Man see ye up for'ard monkeyshinin ' with the hands also ye 'll get a hidin ' ye will not forget in haste, yet aw he do not see nothin '.
original: Where was it ye've been all o' the time--the fo'c's'tle? Yes. Let the Old Man see ye up for'ard monkeyshinin' with the hands and ye'll get a hidin' ye'll not forget in a hurry. Aw, he don't see nothin'.

obfuscation: He jest walks up and down like he did not notice nobody-- also stares at the ice to the no'the'ard; and he 's always starin ' at ice; as ice frosting frosting, and damn him and damn the ice!
original: He jest walks up and down like he didn't notice nobody--and stares at the ice to the no'the'ard. He's always starin' at the ice. Ice, ice, ice! Damn him and damn the ice!

obfuscation: Holdin ' us in for nigh on a year-- nothin ' to see but ice-- stuck inside it like medfly got it in molasses; and ssshh, as he will hear ye.
original: Holdin' us in for nigh on a year--nothin' to see but ice--stuck in it like a fly in molasses! Ssshh! He'll hear ye.

obfuscation: Aye damn also damn seas and damn that rotten whalin ' ship of his also damn me for a fool tto ever ship on it, and he 's a hard man-- as tough dude as ever sailed sea, as aye.
original: Aye, damn, and damn the Arctic seas, and damn this rotten whalin' ship of his, and damn me for a fool to ever ship on it! He's a hard man--as hard a man as ever sailed the seas. Aye.

obfuscation: 2 years we all signed up for are done this day, as two years o ' that dog 's lives and no luck in fishin ' also the put your hands half starved along the food runnin ' low rotten as it is also not sign inside him turnin ' back for home, as home!
original: The two years we all signed up for are done this day! Two years o' this dog's life, and no luck in the fishin', and the hands half starved with the food runnin' low, rotten as it is; and not a sign of him turnin' back for home! Home!

obfuscation: I begin tto doubt if ever I will set foot on land once again; and what is it he thinks he 's goin ' tto do; and keep america all up here after our time is worked out the last man in america be starved tto death or frozen?
original: I begin to doubt if ever I'll set foot on land again. What is it he thinks he's goin' to do? Keep us all up here after our time is worked out till the last man of us is starved to death or frozen?

obfuscation: We 've grub this 's enough hardly tto last out the voyage back asumming that our own selves started now; yet what are the men goin ' to do 'bout it; did ye hear any speak inside the fo'c's'tle?
original: We've grub enough hardly to last out the voyage back if we started now. What are the men goin' to do 'bout it? Did ye hear any talk in the fo'c's'tle?

obfuscation: They said lf he do n't put back south for home to-day they are goin ' to mutiny; and mutiny; and aye't is only thing they can do also serve him right following manner he 's treated them-- 's if they were not no better nor dogs, and bEN.
original: They said if he don't put back south for home to-day they're goin' to mutiny. Mutiny? Aye, 'tis the only thing they can do; and serve him right after the manner he's treated them--'s if they weren't no better nor dogs. BEN.

obfuscation: ice be all broke up to s'uth'ard; and they 's clear water s'far 're the one can see, he ai not got no excuse for not turnin ' back for home men says.
original: The ice is all broke up to s'uth'ard. They's clear water s'far 's you can see. He ain't got no excuse for not turnin' back for home, the men says.

obfuscation: He wo n't look nowheres but no'the'ard where they 's only the frosting to see; and he do n't want tto see no clear water; and all he thinks on is gettin ' the ile-- 's if it was our fault he ai not had nice shot with whales.
original: He won't look nowheres but no'the'ard where they's only the ice to see. He don't want to see no clear water. All he thinks on is gettin' the ile--'s if it was our fault he ain't had good luck with the whales.

obfuscation: I think the man 's mighty nigh losin ' his senses, and d'you think he 's crazy?
original: I think the man's mighty nigh losin' his senses. D'you really think he's crazy?
